last_episode_to_air.name: Really? It’s Over?
last_episode_to_air.overview: XO-IQ tries to rescue their beleaguered performance. Romantic tensions mount as the band receives an offer that could change their lives.

name: Make It Pop
overview: What do an aspiring pop diva, a fashionista and a book worm have in common? Music! After being randomly selected to room together at Mackendrick Prep, Sun Hi, Jodi and Corki must learn to live together in harmony... literally. Can they achieve pop stardom in a school where academics come first and the arts come last? How will these rising stars balance music, grades, relationships and crushes? There's only one way to find out! Get ready for fun, drama, and musical comedy with a K-pop twist and an EDM beat!

episodes.name: Rumors & Roommates
episodes.overview: Sun Hi, Jodi and Corki start life at MacKendrick Prep boarding school with big expectations and bigger dreams all of which might unravel because of a secret Corki refuses to reveal.

episodes.name: Duet
episodes.overview: When Corki moans about her roommates to the principal it causes tensions to increase between Corki and Sun H.

episodes.name: Failed Dreams
episodes.overview: The girls make plans to audition for the school musical together. Caleb tries to earn the girls' forgiveness.

episodes.name: Stolen Moves
episodes.overview: The band and the Spirit Squad start a rivalry over some dance moves. Sun Hi attempts to find out everything about Corki's secret past.

episodes.name: I Can’t Hear Me
episodes.overview: After Sun Hi loses her voice, XO-IQ attempts to deal with a show scheduling conflict. Jared attempts to get Mr. Stark to change the school play.

episodes.name: Popular
episodes.overview: It is homecoming week and the school wonders who will run for king and queen. Caleb is punished with having to do some school chores.

episodes.name: The Situation
episodes.overview: The girls have to bunk with Valerie when a safety issue forces a scramble in dorm rooms. Will everyone survive such close quarters, and will Jared find out Corki's Masked Girl secret?

episodes.name: The Campaign
episodes.overview: The recent revelation that Corki is Masked Girl makes running for Homecoming court against Valerie a whole lot harder.

episodes.name: I Am Genius
episodes.overview: Sun Hi has to go to the principal's office after taking an aptitude test. Corki's homecoming dress vanishes.

episodes.name: Homecoming
episodes.overview: Caleb and the girls make plans to have a secret party. Jodi and Corki try and decide what to wear to the homecoming dance.

episodes.name: Mr. Chang
episodes.overview: Caleb attempts to get XO-IQ a radio interview. When Corki's father shows up it jeopardizes the band's radio interview.

episodes.name: Fashion Truck
episodes.overview: Jodi pays a visit to her fashion idol's shop. Corki needs to keep the band secret from her dad.

episodes.name: The Troll
episodes.overview: Jodi and Caleb grow closer as they work on the musical together. Jared takes charge of the play.

episodes.name: The Tutor
episodes.overview: Valerie becomes Jodi's tutor. Jared needs Corki's help to try and turn Valerie into a better actress.

episodes.name: Talent Show Redux
episodes.overview: Corki and the play suffer when Jared takes total creative control. Sun Hi has to help Mr. Stark come back to reality after he becomes obsessed with his online fans. Caleb and Jodi try to convince Jared to approve their work on the play.

episodes.name: The Curse of Reality
episodes.overview: Sun Hi puts a curse on the play and Mr. Stark after she steals his spotlight.

episodes.name: Eggs
episodes.overview: Relationships end up being put to the test as the students are assigned to take care of an egg as part of a parenting class.

episodes.name: Love and Detention
episodes.overview: The friends end up getting a detention just a couple of days before the play's premiere.

episodes.name: Dreams
episodes.overview: The girls need to take control of the production from Valerie and the Spirit Squad.

episodes.name: Heart, Courage, Brains
episodes.overview: It's show time! With almost no rehearsal, are the kids able to rise to the occasion and save the theater program and Mr. Stark's job? At Ry Ri, some big surprises await them, along with a decision the group will have to make together.

episodes.name: Think
episodes.overview: Sun Hi holds auditions for a new band, while Corki builds a robot, “Chip,” for Think Fest. Jodi meets Alex at their fashion internship.

episodes.name: Robomania
episodes.overview: Sun Hi tries for a solo career, while Jodi’s internship makes her miss a date with Caleb. Corki reprograms “Chip” to be flashier.

episodes.name: My Way or the Highway
episodes.overview: Corki searches for her missing robot, who’s busy giving romantic advice to Caleb. Sun Hi and Linc work on a duet and butt heads.

episodes.name: Oh, Boys
episodes.overview: Sun Hi and Linc try to overcome their off-stage differences, while Caleb plans romantic gestures for Jodi. Chip and Jared face off.

episodes.name: Potato Power
episodes.overview: Sun Hi tries to fire Linc, while Corki enters Chip into Think Fest. Jodi, Caleb and Alex cause a disaster at Hye Jung’s store.

episodes.name: The Mirror
episodes.overview: Sun Hi’s sister, Sun Mi, arrives for Family Week, while Jodi deals with the disaster at Hye Jung’s store. Jared tries to impress Corki’s father with magic.

episodes.name: It’s a Twin Thing
episodes.overview: Corki spies on Linc’s new band, while Jodi juggles her internship and meeting Caleb’s parents. Sun Hi and Sun Mi have a Twin War.

episodes.name: Fashion 911!
episodes.overview: Corki finds a venue for Jodi’s impending fashion show. Sun Hi negotiates for a fresh hit song with Caleb’s new agent, Valerie.

episodes.name: Spring Fling
episodes.overview: Sun Hi discovers part of Linc’s past, while Jodi shows Hye Jung her new design. Corki helps Jared with his college acceptance letters.

episodes.name: Submission Impossible
episodes.overview: Sun Hi, Corki, and Heather race to finish XO-IQ’s Band Blast submission on time, while Jodi and Darmala, the drummer for Linc’s band, get stuck in an elevator.

episodes.name: Scuttlebutt
episodes.overview: Jodi handles gossip, while Sun Hi pleads with DJ Maxwell to let XO-IQ into the Band Blast music competition. Corki and Jared share quality time.

episodes.name: Triangles
episodes.overview: Mr. Stark becomes XO-IQ’s band mentor. Meanwhile, Caleb and Heather hatch a plan to make Jodi jealous. Corki recruits Band Blast roadies.

episodes.name: Get On The Bus!
episodes.overview: XO-IQ and Linc’s band miss the bus to Band Blast. Meanwhile, Corki and Jared practice having a long-distance relationship after he graduates.

episodes.name: Reality Bites
episodes.overview: When the kids arrive at their Band Blast hotel, they are interviewed by Stefan, a behind-the-scenes director with his own agenda.

episodes.name: Band Blast Off
episodes.overview: The Band Blast judges pair XO-IQ and L3 to sing a “band duet,” but the teens’ off-stage hijinks put their on-stage careers in jeopardy.

episodes.name: Staged and Confused
episodes.overview: Sun Hi deals with a major distraction, while Jodi and Caleb discover a rival band stealing an XO-IQ song. Corki is frustrated by Jared’s crazy behavior.

episodes.name: Excess Baggage
episodes.overview: The Band Blast bus has mechanical trouble; Sun Hi and Linc search for cell service; Jodi and Corki organize the group.

episodes.name: Im-Prom-Tu
episodes.overview: Still stranded, the teens stage a “Fake Prom.” The event puts strain on Sun Hi and Linc. Jared does his best to spy on Corki.

episodes.name: Looking For Trouble
episodes.overview: XO-IQ prepares for an important performance. Linc reveals his summer plans to Sun Hi, and Caleb and Jodi deal with a big problem.

episodes.name: Really? It’s Over?
episodes.overview: XO-IQ tries to rescue their beleaguered performance. Romantic tensions mount as the band receives an offer that could change their lives.
